  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 20:27-28",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 20:27-28",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jehoshaphat in the fore-front of them — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They marched all in a body, in solemn procession, and Jehoshaphat at their head, that the country, as they passed along, might join with them in their praises. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "To go again to Jerusalem with joy — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That they might give thanks for the mercy there, where by prayer they had obtained it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Unto the house of the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To renew their praises in the court of the temple, the proper and usual place for it. Praising God must not be the work of a day only; but our praises, when we have received mercy, must be often repeated, as our prayers were, when we were in pursuit of it. Every day we must bless God; as long as we live, and while we have any being, we must praise him, spending our time in that work, in which we hope to spend our eternity.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
